  "body": "Looking at `process_transfer`, I am wondering why do we check that balances are above zero? This would always be the case unless MIN_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT is zero. I'm not sure it's necessary to add this operation, but maybe I am missing something. \r\n\r\n```python\r\n    # Verify balances are not dust\r\n    assert not (0 < state.balances[transfer.sender] < MIN_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT)\r\n    assert not (0 < state.balances[transfer.recipient] < MIN_DEPOSIT_AMOUNT)\r\n```",
